# CODEOWNERS — DORMANT until a second reviewer exists.
#
# Maps high-risk areas to a reviewer. It is INERT today because the protect-main
# ruleset keeps `required_approving_review_count: 0` and `require_code_owner_review:
# false` — a sole owner cannot approve their own PR, so requiring a review would lock
# merges. Until then the L1-high-risk acknowledgment gate is the enforcement.
#
# To turn this into a real second-person review:
#   1. add the reviewer as a collaborator and set them as the owner below,
#   2. flip the ruleset: required_approving_review_count -> 1, require_code_owner_review -> true
#      (via scripts/bootstrap_repo.sh's ruleset JSON or a gh api PUT).
#
# Keep aligned with .github/high-risk-paths (gitignore-style globs here, not fnmatch).

/src/backend/**/agent/           @liubrend
/src/backend/**/db/changelog/    @liubrend
